        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Problem: Skills page had hardcoded English strings in grouping labels (\"Built-in Skills\", \"Workspace Skills\", etc.), status chips (\"eligible\", \"blocked\", \"bundled\", \"disabled\"), and missing-requirement prefixes (\"bin:\", \"env:\", \"config:\", \"os:\") when using Simplified Chinese locale.\r\n- Why it matters: Non-English users see English labels in skill group headers, status badges, and dependency warnings.\r\n- What changed: Extracted all hardcoded strings from `ui/src/ui/views/skills-grouping.ts` and `ui/src/ui/views/skills-shared.ts` into i18n keys, added translations to both `en.ts` and `zh-CN.ts`. Updated `computeSkillMissing()` and `computeSkillReasons()` to emit localized prefixes/reasons.\r\n- What did NOT change (scope boundary): No functional behavior, logic, or styling changed. No new features added. Skill names and descriptions from skill manifests remain in English. No other locales touched.\r\n\r\n## Change Type (select all)\r\n\r\n- [ ] Bug fix\r\n- [ ] Feature\r\n- [ ] Refactor required for the fix\r\n- [ ] Docs\r\n- [ ] Security hardening\r\n- [x] Chore/infra\r\n\r\n## Scope (select all touched areas)\r\n\r\n- [ ] Gateway / orchestration\r\n- [ ] Skills / tool execution\r\n- [ ] Auth / tokens\r\n- [ ] Memory / storage\r\n- [ ] Integrations\r\n- [ ] API / contracts\r\n- [x] UI / DX\r\n- [ ] CI/CD / infra\r\n\r\n## Linked Issue/PR\r\n\r\n- Closes #\r\n- Related #\r\n- [ ] This PR fixes a bug or regression\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\r\n\r\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Skills page grouping labels, status chips, and missing-requirement prefixes were not localized to Simplified Chinese.\r\n- Real environment tested: Local dev gateway (`pnpm gateway:dev`).\r\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Built UI assets with `pnpm ui:build`, started gateway, opened Control UI Skills tab.\r\n- Evidence after fix: Screenshot — group label (内置技能), status chip (已阻止), missing 